description: Research, analyze, produce all-source assessments focusing Geo-Political developments and issues including political leadership, regional relations, economic, and various other topics under the geo-political spectrum. Produces in-depth intelligence assessments on Geopolitical issues concerning area of focus and inputs a wide variety of sources into coherent assessments. Prepares and briefs products for the CENTCOM Commander, leadership and international representatives. Prepares congressional testimonies for Commanding Officer. Identifies intelligence gaps, coordinates collection requirements to meet current and anticipated intelligence needs. Evaluates intelligence reporting, and recommends areas of production and collection emphasis. Maintains awareness of political capabilities, important factors within Iran, in terms of activities, developments, patterns and trends as well as regime stability and dynamics, national security strategy and relations with neighboring countries. Develops and maintains liaison with counterparts within the agency, other national intelligence agencies and components of US commands to coordinate intelligence assessments. Participates in and helps plan conferences, meetings exercises and working groups. Serves as subject matter expert for planning teams, working groups, and planning projects. Served as team lead during exercises. Mentors and guides less experience analysts. Participates in intelligence exchanges. Produces various analytical products distributed throughout the intelligence community.

description: Responsible for teaching company level intelligence concept to soldiers preparing for deployment. Course included instruction on the use of intelligence surveillance and reconnaissance assets, development of priority intelligence requirements, conducting pre-briefing/de-briefings, identifying enemy tactics techniques and procedures, understating the operations and intelligence cycle, pattern and trend analysis, building link diagrams and various other tools of analysis. Instructed students on developing communication plans, utilizing overlay and situation maps, and historical data to conduct analysis, identifying intelligence gaps, conducting targeting meetings, key leader engagements, developing courses of action, most likely course of actions, most deadly courses of actions, and understanding/ and requesting RFIs (requests for information), creating/using SOPs (standard operating procedures).. Instructed students on company level lethal and non-lethal targets. Instructed how to use various programs including analyst notebook and AXISPro (link diagram programs). Promoted after 8 months as an instructor to to team lead and senior instructor. Responsible for scheduling trips for team, train new team members, write trip reports, approve team member reports, conduct evaluations, assist in course development, complete weekly reports and various other tasks. Tasked to be the co-creator of the Homeland Security Civil Authorities Support Team course, working directly with various homeland security officials.
